Blowing the Whistle on Reckless Spending

AFP Weekly Newsletter

  I have a story to tell you. A story of how our sister organization, Americans for Prosperity Foundation, is holding government accountable for wasteful spending.   

 Read the story

 AFPF's Eric Bolinder noticed something fishy. The government agency charged with running Medicaid was refusing to release a report to two U.S. senators on how the agency spends YOUR money. 

So Bolinder submitted a Freedom of Information Act request, asking for details about $143 billion in improper Medicaid payments. The request has been ignored by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid. 

Now, AFPF has filed suit against the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services.  

This type of reckless, unaccountable spending leads to lower quality care for Americans who need it most. It is crucial that lawmakers at the state and federal level work hard to ensure Medicaid money is spent wisely, without waste, fraud and abuse.

Separately, AFP is advocating for a better health care system that has less government control and offer more personal options. Click here to learn more.

 In Other News

  Five Reasons Not to Expand the ACA

Sen. Bernie Sanders wants the government to have even more control over your health care. As a matter of fact, 40 percent of the new spending in his massive $3.5 trillion "infrastructure" plan is dedicated to expanding government-funded insurance. This is a bigger expenditure than all of Obamacare. 

In a new blog post, AFP's Dean Clancy spells out why this new plan is a terrible idea: 

It will drive up health care costs and premiums.

It’s a huge giveaway to insurance companies.

It’s welfare for the wealthy.

It endangers millions of families' hard-won workplace health benefits.

It's a monumental waste of taxpayer money.

You can help us stop Sen. Sanders' health care heist by clicking here.  

Sincerely, 

Tim Phillips

President

Americans for Prosperity
